WEBVTT

01:26.587 --> 01:30.614
<i>[Siren Wailing]</i>

01:53.447 --> 01:56.439
<i>[Sirens Continue Wailing]</i>

02:09.562 --> 02:13.158
<i>[Baby Crying In Distance]</i>

02:40.761 --> 02:44.788
<i>[Bell Tolling]</i>

02:51.972 --> 02:54.702
Hey, watch where you're
going, you old klutz...

02:54.808 --> 02:57.333
- Sorry. Sorry.
- You gonna pick that up?

02:57.444 --> 02:59.344
Pervert.

02:59.446 --> 03:02.074
You're late. I've been
looking all over for you.

03:02.183 --> 03:05.346
I slept right through the alarm clock.
That baby kept me up all night.

03:05.452 --> 03:09.718
- What baby?
- I don't know. Our neighbors have a kid?

03:09.823 --> 03:12.348
Our neighbors are 90 years old.

03:14.695 --> 03:16.959
You want to try and get
the paint on the canvas.

03:17.064 --> 03:18.759
I like it messy.

03:18.866 --> 03:23.098
Oh, yeah?
I gotta go.

03:25.506 --> 03:27.474
Hey-

03:34.348 --> 03:38.978
<i>[Woman] I just start drinking</i>
<i>and doing a lot of, like, pills.</i>

03:39.086 --> 03:42.317
'Cause then it just kills the pain,
and then I can just deal with it later.

03:42.423 --> 03:44.584
<i>[Continues, Indistinct]</i>

03:44.692 --> 03:46.922
I'm just saying- I'm not
telling you to go drink.

03:47.027 --> 03:50.793
I know you go to meetings.
I'm just telling you what works for me, okay?

03:50.898 --> 03:55.164
It's hard to deal with those feelings.
Well, drinking kills feelings. That's why.

03:57.171 --> 03:59.264
It's gonna hail this afternoon.

03:59.373 --> 04:03.571
You think?
Looks pretty sunny to me.

04:03.677 --> 04:06.271
Who the fuck are you?

04:06.380 --> 04:09.315
I'm Dr. Sam Foster.
You must be Henry.

04:09.416 --> 04:11.850
Where's Dr. Levy?

04:11.952 --> 04:14.318
Didn't she get in touch with you?

04:14.421 --> 04:16.480
No.

04:16.589 --> 04:19.559
Oh, I'm sorry.
She's away for a while.

04:19.660 --> 04:22.356
- I'm covering for her.
- She's away where?

04:22.463 --> 04:25.489
She's not feeling well.
She'll be back in a couple of weeks.

04:26.900 --> 04:29.801
What are you-
a substitute shrink?

04:31.639 --> 04:34.472
I guess you could call me that.

04:34.575 --> 04:37.373
Oh.

04:37.478 --> 04:39.639
This is her office.

04:39.747 --> 04:44.616
Yeah, we share it. I'm only here
a few hours a week. Please take a seat.

04:44.718 --> 04:47.186
<i>Oh, I see.</i>

04:47.288 --> 04:51.156
So you treat the, uh...

04:51.258 --> 04:54.352
depressed investment bankers,
paranoid housewives all week?

04:54.461 --> 04:57.726
Come up here to do
a little pro bono work?

04:57.831 --> 04:59.731
It's the other way around.

04:59.833 --> 05:03.735
The bankers are paranoid,
and the housewives are depressed.

05:05.739 --> 05:10.369
<i>Now, you're a junior at the college.</i>
<i>Is that right? Majoring in fine art?</i>

05:13.747 --> 05:17.205
She passed me off to you, huh?

05:19.620 --> 05:22.885
You get the hard cases.

05:22.990 --> 05:27.051
Does it make you uncomfortable
that I'm filling in for her?

05:29.697 --> 05:32.393
She was trying to help me.

05:32.499 --> 05:34.558
I'll try and help you too.

05:36.337 --> 05:39.898
She afraid of me?
Is that why she's gone?

05:40.007 --> 05:42.237
Did I scare her?

05:42.343 --> 05:45.073
Should she be afraid of you?

05:58.225 --> 06:00.420
I've read your file.

06:00.527 --> 06:03.087
And can I read your file?

06:04.798 --> 06:06.891
Tell me why you're here.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.093
I thought you read the file.

06:09.203 --> 06:13.071
You torched your car.
Why?

06:15.442 --> 06:17.342
I don't remember.
I just woke up...

06:17.444 --> 06:20.140
and I was in the car,
and it was on fire.

06:20.247 --> 06:24.149
Is that something you do-
set fires?

06:27.588 --> 06:29.886
I didn't mean to hurt anybody.

06:31.258 --> 06:34.284
Who did you hurt?

06:37.564 --> 06:40.658
I don't know.
I'm gonna go.

06:40.768 --> 06:43.236
No. Please, sit down.
We have more time.

06:43.337 --> 06:46.238
No, I, uh- I'm gonna go home
before this hail starts.

06:46.340 --> 06:50.777
<i>[Woman] The king of Poland goes hunting</i>
<i>in the woods with one ofhis assistants.</i>

06:50.878 --> 06:52.778
And they're looking around...

06:52.880 --> 06:56.338
and suddenly on the other side
of the clearing a farmer walks by.

06:56.450 --> 06:58.918
Hold still.

06:59.019 --> 07:01.180
And the king raises his rifle,
and the farmer yells...

07:01.288 --> 07:03.256
"I'm not a moose."

07:03.357 --> 07:06.190
The king shoots
and kills the guy...

07:06.293 --> 07:08.193
and the assistant's shocked.

07:08.295 --> 07:10.559
And he says...

07:10.664 --> 07:14.293
"Sire, the man said,
'I'm not a moose."'

07:14.401 --> 07:18.303
"Oh," says the king.
"I thought he said, 'I <i>am</i> a moose."'

07:22.109 --> 07:24.202
It's a joke.

07:24.311 --> 07:26.745
No, I'm just trying
to figure out...

07:26.847 --> 07:29.907
if I'm the king or the farmer.

07:31.452 --> 07:34.546
You're the moose.

07:34.655 --> 07:38.614
- I'm the moose?
- Yeah.

07:38.725 --> 07:41.558
[Laughing]

07:41.662 --> 07:44.392
Well, I appear to be the moose.

07:45.933 --> 07:48.993
- It's shit.
- It's not shit.

07:50.337 --> 07:53.170
It's not shit.

08:03.684 --> 08:06.312
Still there.

08:06.420 --> 08:09.116
Sometimes I forget.

08:12.292 --> 08:14.852
They're from another life.

08:26.974 --> 08:29.943
<i>[Thunderclap]</i>

08:31.111 --> 08:33.078
Oh, my God.

08:33.179 --> 08:36.876
#<i>[Radio. ; '60s Pop]</i>

08:44.558 --> 08:46.958
I love this song.

08:49.563 --> 08:52.225
<i>[Indistinct Voices]</i>

08:56.837 --> 09:01.570
<i>I know you. Psych 221.</i>
<i>Professor Azzopardi?</i>

09:03.877 --> 09:07.108
You did that presentation on psychosis
and Tristan Rï¿ªveur, right?

09:07.214 --> 09:10.411
No smoking on the train.

09:12.219 --> 09:15.086
<i>Look at the sign, fella.</i>
<i>No smoking.</i>

09:18.492 --> 09:21.518
<i>Capisce?</i> Put it out.

09:21.628 --> 09:24.028
<i>"Capisce"?</i>

09:26.833 --> 09:30.064
Put out the fucking cigarette.

09:41.615 --> 09:44.516
You oughta be locked up,
you asshole.

09:44.618 --> 09:48.110
<i>[Indistinct Voices]</i>

09:51.391 --> 09:53.382
<i>[Indistinct Subway Announcement]</i>

09:53.493 --> 09:56.758
<i>Beth? Sam. I hope</i>
<i>you're getting some rest.</i>

09:58.532 --> 10:01.626
Look, I met with your
patient today- Henry Letham.

10:01.735 --> 10:04.295
I'd really like
to talk to you about him.

10:04.404 --> 10:07.805
Give me a call, okay?
I wanna hear your voice.

10:09.476 --> 10:13.276
You don't think it's a little odd-
predicting a hailstorm like that?

10:13.380 --> 10:15.507
So he watches the Weather Channel.

10:15.616 --> 10:18.949
No. I looked in the newspaper.
There was nothing about hail today.

10:20.420 --> 10:22.388
How's Beth?

10:22.489 --> 10:26.118
I don't know.
She hasn't returned any of my calls.

10:26.226 --> 10:28.387
She always kinda
liked you, didn't she?

10:30.664 --> 10:33.132
What, are you jealous?

10:33.233 --> 10:35.133
Of Beth?

10:35.235 --> 10:38.136
- I'm just faking it.
- Your students love you.

10:38.238 --> 10:41.901
My students love me
'cause I give 'em all A's.

10:42.009 --> 10:46.173
I mean, what the fuck do I know?
This kid could be the next Rothko.

10:49.483 --> 10:52.384
[Sighs]

10:56.023 --> 10:58.821
<i>[Shoes Drop]</i>

11:02.295 --> 11:04.422
Tell me I'm good.

11:04.531 --> 11:06.431
You're good.

11:06.533 --> 11:09.161
Tell me they'll remember me.

11:09.269 --> 11:11.737
Who's "they"?

11:11.838 --> 11:14.329
The world.

11:14.441 --> 11:17.342
Is that what you want?

11:20.514 --> 11:22.709
The world will remember you.

11:25.686 --> 11:28.052
Now take off your clothes.

11:45.639 --> 11:46.901
Hey.

11:55.148 --> 11:57.708
Who did that?

11:57.818 --> 11:59.945
My girlfriend.

12:00.053 --> 12:02.385
Where'd you get that?

12:02.489 --> 12:05.754
This? I bought it.

12:11.765 --> 12:14.290
Henry, what are you
doing here? l-

12:14.401 --> 12:17.564
I wasn't expecting you.
I have someone coming in.

12:25.679 --> 12:28.842
So, have you considered
a career in meteorology?

12:28.949 --> 12:30.507
Hmm?

12:30.617 --> 12:34.348
The weatherman
said something about hail?

12:34.454 --> 12:37.116
The weatherman?

12:38.592 --> 12:40.492
No.

12:42.195 --> 12:45.323
You know, I can't even
listen to him anymore?

12:48.068 --> 12:50.969
I don't understand a word
that comes out of his mouth.

12:51.071 --> 12:53.301
You don't understand
the weatherman?

12:53.406 --> 12:55.306
No.

12:58.211 --> 13:00.839
But you do?

13:00.947 --> 13:03.973
Sure. He says rain,
I bring an umbrella.

13:10.624 --> 13:13.422
Henry, give me something.

13:15.162 --> 13:17.892
I'm good at what I do.

13:19.633 --> 13:22.193
Well, I'm hearing voices now.

13:24.104 --> 13:26.197
Voices?

13:29.075 --> 13:33.512
They come and they go,
but when they are there-

13:33.613 --> 13:36.309
You're hearing them now?

13:36.416 --> 13:38.577
Okay.

13:41.688 --> 13:44.657
Can you write down
what they're saying?

13:50.697 --> 13:53.393
[Phone Rings]

13:53.500 --> 13:55.934
- Yeah?
- <i>[Man On Intercom]</i>
<i>Hey, Dr. Foster. It's Frederick.</i>

13:56.036 --> 13:57.936
<i>[Lock Buzzing]</i>

14:04.978 --> 14:07.276
Can you read it to me?

14:08.548 --> 14:11.142
- Hmm?
- Can you read it to me?

14:13.320 --> 14:15.618
Uh, yeah.

14:15.722 --> 14:18.486
"Hey, Dr. Foster. It's Frederick."

14:20.060 --> 14:24.087
This is-This voice isn't in your head.
This is a real voice.

14:28.568 --> 14:32.265
Okay. Well, I don't know.

14:32.372 --> 14:35.398
Maybe you could show me
how to tell the difference?

14:36.877 --> 14:38.777
Go on.

14:38.879 --> 14:40.779
I don't know.

14:43.650 --> 14:46.414
<i>[Indistinct Voices]</i>

14:46.519 --> 14:49.955
"I didn't move him.
I know you're not supposed to move 'em."

14:50.056 --> 14:53.082
"I can't watch anymore."

14:53.193 --> 14:58.324
"Stay with me, Henry.
Stay with me."

14:58.431 --> 15:02.663
<i>Hey, guys. Sorry</i>
<i>to interrupt, but, uh</i>- 

15:02.769 --> 15:05.499
Hey, Frederick,
can you give me a minute?

15:05.605 --> 15:08.802
- I've got a conference call at 11:00.
- Just a minute. Thank you.

15:08.909 --> 15:11.275
Yeah, okay.

15:15.649 --> 15:18.675
Where's this from?

15:19.920 --> 15:22.684
Oh, I burned myself.

15:22.789 --> 15:25.451
You burned yourself? Why?

15:28.261 --> 15:30.320
Practicing for hell.

15:31.765 --> 15:33.995
Why do you think
you're going to hell?

15:34.100 --> 15:36.295
Um...

15:39.906 --> 15:41.806
'cause of what I did.

15:43.376 --> 15:45.640
What I'm gonna do.

15:45.745 --> 15:48.373
What are you gonna do?

15:55.288 --> 15:57.552
You're gonna try and kill yourself?

15:59.225 --> 16:01.659
And how seriously should I take that?

16:01.761 --> 16:04.457
Saturday at midnight
is when I'm gonna do it.

16:04.564 --> 16:07.158
You gotta know that
everything just changed.

16:07.267 --> 16:10.566
If you talk to me about suicide,
I'm required to take certain actions.

16:10.670 --> 16:14.071
Hey, look. Just wait a second.
Wait a second.

16:14.174 --> 16:15.308
Just, you know, deal with him...

16:15.308 --> 16:18.334
Just, you know, deal with him...

16:18.445 --> 16:22.472
and, uh, we'll talk
about it next time.

16:22.582 --> 16:25.016
There's a next time?

16:25.118 --> 16:27.018
Yeah.

16:27.120 --> 16:29.213
Yeah.

16:31.725 --> 16:34.421
Yeah, we got three days.

16:35.762 --> 16:37.662
<i>[Door Closes]</i>

16:37.764 --> 16:40.096
<i>He's coming.! He's coming.!</i>

16:40.200 --> 16:45.228
I am not a monster, goddamn you!
Get off of me!

16:45.338 --> 16:48.705
<i>[Man] Nobody's calling you a monster,</i>
<i>Daisy. Come on now.</i>

16:48.808 --> 16:52.039
<i>[Daisy] Please.! You said you would</i>- 
<i>I don't deserve this.!</i>

16:52.145 --> 16:55.512
Well, if you'd just remember to take your pills,
you wouldn't have to go through this.

16:55.615 --> 16:59.608
- I'm not a monster. I'm lovable.
- I know you are.

16:59.719 --> 17:03.280
[Grunts]
I'm lovable. Stop!

17:03.390 --> 17:06.415
- No, please! I'm lovable.
- Very lovable.

17:06.526 --> 17:09.256
He's coming!
I oughta know he's coming!

17:09.362 --> 17:12.888
I'll be good. I'll be good!
I don't want to- No!

17:12.999 --> 17:14.898
- Hey, Sammy.
- Hey.

17:15.001 --> 17:17.595
He's just a kid!
He's just a kid!

17:17.704 --> 17:20.537
Okay, now.
Let go, Daisy.

17:20.640 --> 17:22.972
He's just a kid!

17:23.076 --> 17:24.976
<i>He's just a kid.!</i>

17:25.078 --> 17:27.637
Sorry about that.
You okay?

17:27.747 --> 17:31.649
Yeah. Yeah. I'm used to dealing
with neurotic stockbrokers.

17:31.751 --> 17:34.015
<i>Neurotic stockbrokers pay better.</i>

17:35.955 --> 17:38.480
<i>So, uh, what brings you</i>
<i>to Club Meds?</i>

17:38.591 --> 17:40.991
I have a student
threatening to kill himself.

17:41.094 --> 17:44.120
Christ. Well, tell him
to take a number.

17:44.230 --> 17:46.130
Look, you know how it works.

17:46.232 --> 17:48.962
If he threatens to hurt
himself or someone else...

17:49.069 --> 17:52.197
then we can take him in,
but we can't hold him here forever.

17:52.305 --> 17:54.364
He said he's gonna
do it on Saturday.

17:54.474 --> 17:56.635
If you take him in now,
he'll be out by then.

17:56.743 --> 17:59.576
Organized kid.
He's got it all scheduled.

17:59.679 --> 18:02.204
Saturday, midnight.
That's what he said.

18:03.583 --> 18:06.711
We can pick him up Friday,
hold him for the weekend.

18:06.820 --> 18:09.380
As you can see, it's
not a real fun process.

18:09.489 --> 18:12.117
Anything you could do to avoid it?

18:12.225 --> 18:14.819
- What have you got him on?
- He won't take any meds.

18:40.053 --> 18:42.419
<i>[Door Opens]</i>

18:44.591 --> 18:47.185
<i>[Woman]</i>
<i>Where's my man?</i>

18:49.329 --> 18:51.820
<i>You know what I've</i>
<i>been craving all day?</i>

18:56.603 --> 18:59.197
Something to drink.

19:04.611 --> 19:07.205
What's the matter?
You're looking a little tense.

19:07.313 --> 19:09.679
<i>It's nothing.</i>

19:09.782 --> 19:12.410
So tell me about nothing.

19:15.021 --> 19:16.921
I'm just tired.

19:17.023 --> 19:20.584
Let me make a call,
and then we can take a bath together.

19:23.730 --> 19:26.062
<i>Beth, it's Sam again.</i>

19:26.166 --> 19:28.862
<i>Um, I hope</i>
<i>you're getting some rest.</i>

19:28.968 --> 19:32.734
Everyone's been asking about you.
Look, give me a call.

19:32.839 --> 19:37.208
I want to speak to you about Henry Letham
and find out how you're feeling, okay?

19:38.444 --> 19:40.344
Bye.

19:42.949 --> 19:45.884
<i>You sound like you're talking</i>
<i>to one of your patients.</i>

19:45.985 --> 19:50.183
- Is she sick?
- She's exhausted.

19:50.290 --> 19:52.224
Exhausted?

19:53.693 --> 19:57.060
Come on. We live in New York City.
Everyone's exhausted.

19:57.163 --> 19:59.495
- [Sighs]
- <i>What, is that a code word?</i>

20:01.000 --> 20:02.900
Yeah.

20:05.038 --> 20:07.029
Yeah, I guess it is.

20:16.382 --> 20:19.283
<i>[Water Running]</i>

20:19.385 --> 20:23.116
[Sighs]
How's the kid with the hail?

20:23.223 --> 20:25.555
Ever heard of
doctor-patient privilege?

20:25.658 --> 20:28.149
What's the prediction
tomorrow? Locusts?

20:28.261 --> 20:30.388
He's confused.

20:30.496 --> 20:33.954
Confused?
Is that like exhausted?

20:34.067 --> 20:36.262
I don't want to get
into this right now.

20:36.369 --> 20:40.271
You told me about the lawyer
who thought her cat was talking to her.

20:40.373 --> 20:42.466
I shouldn't have.

20:46.179 --> 20:48.704
He wants to kill himself.

20:48.815 --> 20:53.081
That's it, isn't it?
That's why you won't talk about it.

20:54.921 --> 20:58.413
- He has a right to confidential counseling.
- Come on, Sam.

21:03.463 --> 21:06.796
He wants to kill himself
on Saturday night.

21:08.234 --> 21:10.930
At midnight, like it's a date.

21:15.975 --> 21:18.102
What's so special about Saturday?

21:18.211 --> 21:21.078
I didn't have time to ask.

21:21.180 --> 21:24.809
Look, we can talk
about it, you know.

21:24.917 --> 21:26.851
It doesn't scare me.

21:26.953 --> 21:30.218
- It scares me.
- Yeah, I know.

21:30.323 --> 21:33.292
But you have to trust me.

21:34.761 --> 21:36.661
I do.

21:48.808 --> 21:51.709
- <i>[Man] Up slow, Jerry.</i>
- <i>[Jerry] Got it.</i>

21:51.811 --> 21:53.711
- <i>Looking good, Mikey.</i>
- <i>[Woman] Not-Not so fast.</i>

21:53.813 --> 21:55.713
- <i>Stop that swaying.</i>
- <i>[Boy] Come on, Mommy. Faster.</i>

21:55.815 --> 21:59.342
Easy. Easy. Hold it!
Stay clear, you guys. Quick.

21:59.452 --> 22:02.853
<i>[Boy]</i>
<i>Wait.! Wait.! My balloon.!</i>

22:02.955 --> 22:05.355
Sorry, kid.
It's gone to balloon heaven.

22:05.458 --> 22:08.393
Oh, that's okay, sir.
We're gonna get another one at the park.

22:08.494 --> 22:10.826
- Go ahead, honey.
- Promise, Mommy?

22:10.930 --> 22:13.228
All right, you guys.
Comin' your way.

22:13.333 --> 22:15.460
<i>Tristan Rï¿ªveur once said...</i>

22:15.568 --> 22:19.664
"If we cannot see the wind,
we can see the wind's will."

22:21.107 --> 22:25.441
Here, Pradilla Ortiz forces us
to imagine the wind...

22:25.545 --> 22:27.536
by showing its effect
on the smoke...

22:27.647 --> 22:31.048
the candle flames
and Doï¿±a Juana's veil.

22:33.286 --> 22:36.847
Only the victims' faces are
visible in Goya's masterwork.

22:38.324 --> 22:42.385
<i>Our eyes are drawn</i>
<i>to the brightest spot on the canvas</i>- 

22:42.495 --> 22:47.432
<i>the white shirt of a doomed man</i>
<i>pleading for his life.</i>

22:47.533 --> 22:50.559
<i>Behind him, the hill closing in...</i>

22:50.670 --> 22:53.969
<i>refusing a path to escape.</i>

22:54.073 --> 22:58.305
- <i>[Indistinct Voices]</i>
- The Dead Toreador <i>was originally</i>
<i>part of a larger painting...</i>

22:58.411 --> 23:01.437
Incident in a Bullfight.

23:01.547 --> 23:06.041
<i>After the painting was mocked</i>
<i>by critics and viewers...</i>

23:06.152 --> 23:08.552
Manet angrily sliced it in half...

23:08.654 --> 23:10.923
removing the fallen hero
from his arena...

23:10.923 --> 23:12.550
removing the fallen hero
from his arena...

23:12.658 --> 23:17.721
<i>and accidentally creating</i>
<i>one ofhis most enduring works.</i>

23:17.830 --> 23:20.560
- Hey.
- Hey.

23:20.666 --> 23:23.100
How are you doing?

23:23.202 --> 23:25.102
Oh, you know.

23:25.204 --> 23:29.368
I didn't know if you'd still be coming
to class after what you told me.

23:29.475 --> 23:32.376
Yeah, well, where else
am I gonna go?

23:32.478 --> 23:34.378
