30:53.485 --> 30:56.283
Ah.
[Laughing]

30:56.388 --> 30:58.413
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

30:58.524 --> 31:00.856
<i>I hear she's a beautiful girl.</i>

31:00.960 --> 31:04.691
How long have you
been carrying that around?

31:04.797 --> 31:06.389
A while.

31:06.498 --> 31:08.693
What are you waiting for?

31:08.801 --> 31:11.736
The fear to go away, I guess.

31:11.837 --> 31:14.135
Mm.

31:14.240 --> 31:16.800
How do I know she won't try again?

31:16.909 --> 31:18.877
You don't know, Sam.

31:18.978 --> 31:21.037
Does she make you happy?

31:21.146 --> 31:23.273
Oh, yes.

31:23.382 --> 31:26.078
Well, here's something that won't.

31:26.185 --> 31:28.983
Knight to C-3.
Check.

31:29.088 --> 31:31.079
- Oh, shit.
- <i>[Laughing]</i>

31:33.392 --> 31:38.295
Do you remember the dream
of the burning boy referred to by Freud?

31:38.397 --> 31:41.093
- Vaguely.
- Vaguely meaning no?

31:41.200 --> 31:43.100
- Right.
- Yeah.

31:43.202 --> 31:46.171
Well, he describes a man
whose child is dying.

31:46.272 --> 31:49.935
The father sits by the boy's bed
night after night...

31:50.042 --> 31:53.500
and after the boy is dead,
they give him a wake.

31:53.612 --> 31:58.845
And they set up a circle of candles
around the boy's body.

31:58.951 --> 32:02.387
And the father's exhausted.
He falls asleep.

32:02.488 --> 32:06.356
And he dreams that his son
is standing beside him...

32:06.492 --> 32:10.428
holding his arm
and whispering...

32:10.529 --> 32:13.191
<i>"Father, can't you see</i>
<i>that I'm burning?"</i>

32:13.299 --> 32:16.132
- You have a visitor?
- Henry.

32:16.235 --> 32:18.226
- I can come back.
- No, no. You're all right.

32:18.337 --> 32:20.362
- I don't mind.
- Do you know Dr. Patterson?

32:20.472 --> 32:23.464
- <i>No.</i>
- Pleased to meet you.

32:29.281 --> 32:32.307
What's the matter, Henry?

32:36.121 --> 32:38.021
[Whispering]
What the fuck?

32:40.159 --> 32:42.389
What are you doing here?

32:42.494 --> 32:45.156
We're playing chess.

32:45.264 --> 32:47.459
You're dead.

32:47.566 --> 32:51.468
- <i>[Patterson] Sam?</i>
- I watched you die.

32:51.570 --> 32:54.130
<i>Sam, we'll finish this game later.</i>

32:54.239 --> 32:56.036
Sure.

32:56.141 --> 32:59.872
- Where are you going?
- Henry, take a seat.

32:59.979 --> 33:03.380
- <i>Why'd you come back?</i>
- Do you know Leon?

33:03.482 --> 33:06.383
What did he say to you?
Did he say something about me?

33:06.485 --> 33:09.579
No, he didn't say anything about you.
I don't think Leon even knows you.

33:11.256 --> 33:14.350
That's my father.

33:14.460 --> 33:16.428
He knows me.

33:16.528 --> 33:19.588
Now, listen, I've known Leon a long time.
He doesn't have any children.

33:19.698 --> 33:22.826
Don't say that! Don't
fuckin' say that to me!

33:22.935 --> 33:26.098
What are you doing?

33:26.205 --> 33:28.673
Do you think I don't
recognize my own father?

33:28.774 --> 33:31.709
- You told me your father was dead.
- He is dead.

33:31.810 --> 33:35.211
He's dead, and that's him
walkin' out the fuckin' door!

33:35.314 --> 33:37.942
The man walking out the door
is alive and well.

33:38.050 --> 33:41.042
What's happening?

33:41.153 --> 33:44.350
I saw all the blood,
and I watched him die.

33:46.458 --> 33:48.392
I did it.

33:48.494 --> 33:51.952
[Sobbing]
It's my fault.

33:52.064 --> 33:54.862
Maybe you hurt someone,
but not Leon.

33:54.967 --> 33:57.629
Who did you hurt?
Your father?

33:57.736 --> 34:02.469
[Sobbing Continues]
I don't remember.

34:02.574 --> 34:06.943
Sometimes we don't want to remember,
but I think you have to try.

34:08.179 --> 34:10.909
Fuck you! What the fuck
do you know!

34:11.016 --> 34:14.918
You don't know anything!
Everything you know is a fuckin' lie!

34:15.020 --> 34:18.012
- All right?
- Okay.

34:18.123 --> 34:20.784
Tell me what the truth is.

34:23.996 --> 34:25.896
