34:25.998 --> 34:29.489
Your troubles will cease,
and fortune will smile upon you.

34:33.871 --> 34:37.170
Your troubles will cease,
and fortune will smile upon you.

34:37.275 --> 34:39.301
<i>Yes, Henry.</i>

34:39.411 --> 34:42.312
Henry?

34:46.284 --> 34:47.684
<i>Henry?</i>

34:49.353 --> 34:51.788
<i>Henry.!</i>

34:56.228 --> 34:58.992
<i>Henry.!</i>

35:01.133 --> 35:03.328
Henry?

35:03.435 --> 35:05.665
Henry, are you there?

35:22.721 --> 35:25.189
Here we go.

35:57.089 --> 35:59.216
Trouble.

36:21.547 --> 36:24.038
[Tape Rewinding]

36:24.149 --> 36:26.583
- [Beeps]
- [Sam's Voice On Recording] Henry, listen.

36:26.685 --> 36:29.279
<i>Stay with me, okay?</i>
<i>Listen to my voice, Henry.</i>

36:29.388 --> 36:33.119
- <i>Stay with us here, all right?</i>
- Is that your voice?

36:35.661 --> 36:38.653
<i>I didn't leave that message.</i>

36:38.764 --> 36:42.097
Probably someone who
sounds exactly like you.

36:42.201 --> 36:44.396
So what do we do now?

36:44.503 --> 36:46.403
Not much we can do
at this point.

36:46.505 --> 36:50.532
We don't have the resources or the manpower
for a stakeout or anything like that.

36:50.642 --> 36:53.076
I'll notify the police,
but they won't do anything.

36:53.178 --> 36:55.078
Why not?

36:55.180 --> 36:59.082
Because they've got more important things
to do than look for depressed college students.

36:59.184 --> 37:00.913
Then I'll find him.

37:01.019 --> 37:02.953
Well, if you do,
give me a call.

37:03.055 --> 37:05.546
We'll pick him up for you.
But do me a favor, Sammy.

37:05.657 --> 37:08.387
The kid hears voices
and carries a gun.

37:08.493 --> 37:10.222
Watch your back.

37:12.064 --> 37:13.964
[Coughing]

37:17.769 --> 37:20.966
Mommy, is that man
gonna die?

37:23.909 --> 37:26.104
Come on, Bobby.
We're gonna be late.

37:26.211 --> 37:29.078
You shouldn't run away from me like that,
you little monkey.

37:29.181 --> 37:31.172
<i>[Boy]</i>
<i>But is he gonna die?</i>

37:36.121 --> 37:38.021
Listen to this.

37:38.123 --> 37:41.024
"Henry Letham has a fertile,
powerful imagination.

37:41.126 --> 37:45.586
If he maintains his concentration,
he will create new worlds with his art."

37:45.697 --> 37:48.461
Jim O'Shea?

37:48.567 --> 37:50.660
Professor O'Shea, yeah.
How'd you know?

37:50.769 --> 37:54.432
'CauseJim wants to fuck
every cute boy in his class.

37:54.539 --> 37:58.703
- Did you ever hear of an artist
named Tristan Rï¿ªveur?
- Yeah, of course.

37:58.810 --> 38:01.506
- Do you like his work?
- I've never seen it. Nobody has.

38:01.613 --> 38:04.104
He burned all his paintings
before he killed himself.

38:04.216 --> 38:06.116
- He killed himself?
- Mm-hmm.

38:06.218 --> 38:08.846
When he was 18, he told everyone
he'd live three more years...

38:08.954 --> 38:11.013
then go to New York
and kill himself.

38:11.123 --> 38:15.059
And that's exactly what he did.
Left a one-line note:

38:15.160 --> 38:19.654
"Un suicide ï¿©lï¿©gant
est I'oeuvre d'art finale."

38:19.765 --> 38:22.632
"An elegant suicide is
the ultimate work of art."

38:22.734 --> 38:26.033
Ah, Jesus.
He's Henry's favorite artist.

38:26.138 --> 38:28.163
Of course he is.

38:30.809 --> 38:33.642
<i>[Water Running]</i>

38:33.745 --> 38:35.713
Let me talk to him.

38:35.814 --> 38:38.146
Talk to him?
First I've gotta find him.

38:38.250 --> 38:42.243
He'll find you. He knows you can help him.
That's exactly why he keeps coming back to you.

38:42.354 --> 38:44.879
Well, even if he does,
I can't let you talk to him.

38:44.990 --> 38:47.015
I'd violate every rule in the book.

38:47.125 --> 38:52.222
So violate them. You have something, Sam.
This kid trusts you.

38:52.331 --> 38:55.994
But you've never stood where
he's standing right now, and he knows that.

38:56.101 --> 39:00.731
Yeah, but I treat people every day
with conditions I've never experienced myself.

39:03.842 --> 39:06.606
You know, the day I did it...

39:06.712 --> 39:10.011
I took two razor blades
to the bathtub.

39:10.115 --> 39:13.380
You know why?

39:13.485 --> 39:18.013
Because I knew that
once I started to bleed, I'd get weak...

39:18.123 --> 39:22.526
and I didn't want to drop one blade
and leave myself half done.

39:24.396 --> 39:26.762
Can you imagine that?

39:26.865 --> 39:29.857
Can you imagine hating
your life so much...

39:29.968 --> 39:32.801
that you want to bring
a backup razor?

39:47.619 --> 39:49.587
So what do I tell him?

39:53.225 --> 39:56.160
There's too much beauty to quit.

39:57.996 --> 40:02.490
Tell him that.
There's too much goddamn beauty.

40:15.280 --> 40:17.180
Eat something.

40:17.282 --> 40:20.115
I'm not hungry.

40:20.218 --> 40:23.119
Eat your fortune cookie.

40:27.025 --> 40:29.289
It's yours.

40:38.270 --> 40:43.207
"Your troubles will cease,
and fortune will smile upon you."

40:43.308 --> 40:45.970
Not a moment too soon.

40:48.079 --> 40:50.013
<i>What's the matter?</i>

40:52.184 --> 40:54.414
[Horn Honking]

41:02.494 --> 41:05.827
<i>[Indistinct Screeching]</i>

41:05.931 --> 41:08.866
- Beth, it's Sam.
- [Woman On Phone] I didn't touch him.

41:08.967 --> 41:11.868
- Beth? Beth?
- I know you're not supposed to move-

41:11.970 --> 41:14.370
<i>[Door Lock Buzzes]</i>

41:16.007 --> 41:18.168
<i>[Elevator Bell Dings]</i>

41:26.151 --> 41:28.984
Beth?

41:30.522 --> 41:32.581
Beth?

41:32.691 --> 41:34.659
It's me.

41:34.759 --> 41:37.922
Are you okay?

41:40.665 --> 41:42.929
I'm gonna turn on the light, okay?

41:50.308 --> 41:54.210
I know Leon's been trying
to get through to you.

41:54.312 --> 41:56.212
And Toni.

42:00.485 --> 42:03.215
<i>Oh, Jesus.</i>

42:05.457 --> 42:09.621
- <i>[Indistinct Voices]</i>
- Beth, are you gonna talk to me?

42:09.728 --> 42:12.424
What do you want to talk about?

42:14.833 --> 42:16.801
How are you feeling?

42:16.902 --> 42:20.394
What do you really
wanna talk about?

42:22.040 --> 42:24.702
I'm worried about you...

42:24.809 --> 42:28.006
and I wanna know more
about Henry Letham.

42:28.113 --> 42:30.274
I didn't touch him.

42:30.382 --> 42:33.374
I know you're not
supposed to move them.

42:33.485 --> 42:35.253
What does that mean?

42:35.253 --> 42:36.151
What does that mean?

42:38.857 --> 42:41.883
I wanna kiss you.
Do you want to play a kissing game?

42:41.993 --> 42:43.392
Beth.

42:45.463 --> 42:48.330
No. You're loyal.

42:48.433 --> 42:52.767
You're a good dog.
Good, loyal dog, Sam.

42:54.239 --> 42:56.230
What's her name?

42:56.341 --> 42:58.241
Lila?

42:58.343 --> 43:01.506
You should've let her
bleed in the bathtub.

43:01.613 --> 43:04.980
- <i>She had the right idea.</i>
- What are you talking about?

43:05.083 --> 43:08.177
It's highly inappropriate.

43:08.286 --> 43:12.347
You're not supposed to fuck your patients,
even the pretty ones.

43:12.457 --> 43:14.482
You know the rules.

43:14.593 --> 43:18.791
- You can't drink while you're taking these.
- Mm. Apparently I can.

43:18.897 --> 43:22.333
No, you can't. Come on, Beth.
I want you to come take a shower.

43:23.635 --> 43:25.296
Bathe the corpse.

43:25.403 --> 43:27.769
We won't really be corpses
though, will we?

43:27.872 --> 43:30.432
It will be more
like a memory of nothing.

43:30.542 --> 43:32.976
<i>What happened to you, Beth?</i>

43:33.078 --> 43:37.378
- I need to sleep, please.
- No, you got too much crap in your system.

43:37.482 --> 43:39.541
Are you okay to shower?

43:39.651 --> 43:42.677
- He's watching us.
- No, we're alone.

43:42.787 --> 43:46.723
- He's watching.
- Are you still talking to him?

43:46.825 --> 43:49.453
- <i>Do you know where he is?</i>
- Ask the mother.

43:49.561 --> 43:52.496
- The mother's dead.
- Is she?

43:52.597 --> 43:54.531
Ask anyway.

43:54.633 --> 43:56.658
Hello? Hello? Yeah.

43:56.768 --> 43:58.998
This is Sam Foster,
Dr. Sam Foster.

43:59.104 --> 44:02.665
I'm a psychiatrist. Yeah.

44:02.774 --> 44:06.301
I'm calling about a student
named Henry Letham.

44:08.079 --> 44:10.206
He is?

44:10.315 --> 44:12.783
This is very strange, Mrs. Letham.

44:12.884 --> 44:17.014
He told me you had passed-
Hello? Hello?

44:17.122 --> 44:19.215
- <i>[Phone Beeps]</i>
- Damn it.

44:22.794 --> 44:25.558
This is it.
I won't be long.

44:32.103 --> 44:34.196
<i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>

44:38.677 --> 44:41.043
<i>[Dog Barks]</i>

44:43.348 --> 44:47.216
- <i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>
- I've been waiting for you.

44:47.318 --> 44:49.252
Mrs. Letham?

44:49.354 --> 44:53.085
I'm Dr. Sam Foster.
I'm sorry to bother you at this hour.

44:53.191 --> 44:55.489
I thought you'd never come.

44:55.593 --> 44:59.689
I would have come earlier.
I didn't know you were here.

44:59.798 --> 45:02.995
It's easy to forget about me...

45:03.101 --> 45:05.194
all alone up here.

45:05.303 --> 45:08.602
Your son's not well.
That's why I'm here.

45:08.707 --> 45:10.607
I'm trying to find him.

45:10.709 --> 45:14.304
I'm sorry to say he's threatened
to commit suicide.

45:14.412 --> 45:18.712
You came to see Olive,
didn't you? Not me.

45:18.817 --> 45:20.876
Olive?

45:20.985 --> 45:25.115
There she is.
She's been lonely.

45:25.223 --> 45:28.124
<i>Me and Olive</i>
<i>keep each other company.</i>

45:28.226 --> 45:31.889
We've been alone in this house
for a thousand years.

45:34.065 --> 45:36.625
Hey, Olive.

45:36.735 --> 45:39.101
How are you doing, girl?

45:39.204 --> 45:41.934
<i>[Mrs. Letham]</i>
<i>She doesn't remember you.</i>

45:44.275 --> 45:47.938
- Are you hungry?
- No.

45:48.046 --> 45:50.241
Do you know
how to contact your son?

45:50.348 --> 45:52.976
Are there any relatives or friends
he might have gone to see?

45:55.620 --> 45:57.781
Let me fix you something to eat.

45:57.889 --> 46:01.484
You stay with Olive.
There's some leftovers in the fridge.

46:04.028 --> 46:07.156
Most days I don't say
a single word.

46:07.265 --> 46:11.099
<i>Sometimes I'm silent so long,</i>
<i>I forget how to speak.</i>

46:16.407 --> 46:19.604
Mrs. Letham,
we have an emergency here.

46:19.711 --> 46:21.611
You-

46:21.713 --> 46:24.546
Do you hate me?

46:26.117 --> 46:28.108
You must hate me.

46:29.454 --> 46:31.615
Is that why you did it?

46:31.723 --> 46:33.953
No, I don't hate you.

46:35.426 --> 46:38.224
<i>I'm here because</i>
<i>your son needs help.</i>

46:39.464 --> 46:42.399
I knew you'd come eventually.

46:42.500 --> 46:46.095
<i>It's been quiet without you.</i>
<i>Lonely.</i>

46:46.204 --> 46:50.504
<i>Mrs. Letham, who do you think I am?</i>

46:50.608 --> 46:53.907
Don't play games.
Not anymore.

46:54.012 --> 46:56.071
Who am I?

46:56.181 --> 46:58.911
You think I don't
know you, Henry?

46:59.017 --> 47:02.077
You think I don't
recognize my only son?

47:02.187 --> 47:06.715
Oh, Lord, I've missed you.
I've missed you so much.

47:07.992 --> 47:10.961
I know you never
meant to hurt us.

47:11.062 --> 47:14.395
- Mom?
- Yes, baby.

47:14.499 --> 47:16.967
How did I hurt you?

47:17.068 --> 47:21.596
It doesn't matter anymore.
I could never stay angry with you.

47:23.641 --> 47:25.609
What do I do on Saturdays?

47:27.946 --> 47:32.474
When you were a boy,
you used to go to the zoo.

47:32.584 --> 47:38.079
Remember? You loved
to watch the walrus swim.

47:38.189 --> 47:40.589
But I'm older now.

47:40.692 --> 47:44.890
<i>It's my 21 st birthday tomorrow.</i>
<i>What'll I do for my birthday?</i>

47:46.497 --> 47:51.457
Who knows?
You don't tell me anything these days.

47:51.569 --> 47:54.538
I guess you tell Athena
your secrets now.

47:54.639 --> 47:58.541
Athena?
Do you remember where Athena lives?

47:58.643 --> 48:00.873
<i>[Woman's Voice]</i>
<i>Dogs are a big responsibility, darling.</i>

48:00.979 --> 48:04.244
- Look at the mess I'm making.
- <i>[Dog Growling]</i>

48:04.349 --> 48:07.147
- I just have to clean it up.
- Let me see your head.

48:07.252 --> 48:09.277
- You don't want to see.
- Mrs. Letham.

48:09.387 --> 48:12.049
You didn't mean to hurt anyone.
You know you didn't.

48:12.156 --> 48:14.647
Let me look at your head.
That's a serious wound.

48:14.759 --> 48:18.422
- Don't look at me, darling. Don't-
- [Dog Barking, Snarling]

48:18.529 --> 48:20.759
- [Whining, Groaning]
- <i>Olive, off!</i>

48:20.865 --> 48:24.392
- [Snarling Continues]
- Olive, off!

48:24.502 --> 48:26.595
Let me fix you something to eat.

48:26.704 --> 48:28.797
[Screams]

48:28.907 --> 48:31.808
You're a bleeder, huh?

48:31.910 --> 48:34.140
Here, maintain pressure on that.

48:34.245 --> 48:36.406
<i>[Knocking]</i>

48:36.514 --> 48:40.541
Dr. Foster?
Could I have a word with you?

48:43.788 --> 48:46.256
<i>Yeah, you got bit up pretty good.</i>

48:46.357 --> 48:49.656
- Get your rabies shot already?
- Yeah.

48:51.262 --> 48:55.926
Look, I'm, uh-
I'm Sheriff Kennelly.

48:56.034 --> 48:59.333
Now, l-I know you already
spoke with Deputy Carlyle...

48:59.437 --> 49:03.168
<i>but I just wanted</i>
<i>to confirm a few things.</i>

49:03.274 --> 49:08.177
You said the, uh- the assault took place
at 9625 Rickover Street?

49:08.279 --> 49:11.214
- That's right.
- The home belonging to the Letham family?

49:11.316 --> 49:14.877
Right. Her dog attacked me,
and... she needs some help.

49:14.986 --> 49:17.511
She has a severe head wound.
She should be in a hospital.

49:17.622 --> 49:19.817
I went to high school
with Maureen Letham.

49:19.924 --> 49:23.291
Oh, yeah? Maybe you know her son, Henry.
He's a patient of mine.

49:23.394 --> 49:26.830
I remember Henry.
Pale, skinny kid, always drawing pictures.

49:26.931 --> 49:30.025
- Yeah, that's him.
- He kind of gave me the creeps.

49:30.134 --> 49:32.694
<i>What's strange, Doctor</i>- 

49:32.804 --> 49:35.170
What I'm trying to figure out is...

49:35.273 --> 49:39.004
who you were speaking with
over there at 9625 Rickover Street.

49:39.110 --> 49:42.238
I'm sorry. I thought we already
established Maureen Letham.

49:42.347 --> 49:45.077
She told you her name
was Maureen Letham?

49:45.183 --> 49:47.208
Yeah. We were talking
about her son.

49:47.318 --> 49:49.752
She wasn't entirely coherent.
She needs medical assistance.

49:49.854 --> 49:52.652
But why did you want to talk
to this woman at 1:00 in the morning?

49:52.757 --> 49:55.419
Look, I'm treating her son.
It's an emergency situation.

49:55.526 --> 49:58.893
The- Sheriff, she needs help.
She's lost a lot of blood.

50:00.231 --> 50:03.758
I told you I went to school
with Maureen Letham.

50:03.868 --> 50:06.428
I also went to her funeral.

50:06.537 --> 50:09.597
She's been dead for months.

50:09.707 --> 50:12.198
Car wreck-
her and her husband.

50:12.310 --> 50:16.144
<i>As far as I know, that house is empty still.</i>
<i>The family's trying to sell it.</i>

50:16.247 --> 50:19.410
I spoke to Maureen Letham
an hour ago.

50:19.517 --> 50:22.918
It's probably just
someone's confused.

50:25.023 --> 50:27.048
So how long they keeping you here?

50:27.158 --> 50:31.060
I don't know. I gotta head back into the city.
Look, 9625 Rickover Street.

50:31.162 --> 50:34.222
I was there.
Henry's mother was there.

50:34.332 --> 50:36.823
All right, Dr. Foster.

50:36.934 --> 50:39.630
We'll be in touch.
I've got your number.

50:44.609 --> 50:47.134
Sheriff?

50:49.480 --> 50:51.573
Sheriff?

50:51.682 --> 50:54.116
- Uh-huh.
- <i>Mrs. Letham</i>- 

50:54.218 --> 50:56.209
Did she have brown eyes?

50:56.320 --> 50:59.812
Oh, no, sir.
Bluest eyes in town.

51:11.903 --> 51:15.304
- <i>[Siren Wailing In Distance]</i>
- <i>[Men Shouting]</i>

51:23.247 --> 51:25.772
<i>[Indistinct Voices]</i>

51:25.883 --> 51:32.914
#<i>[Woman Singing]</i>

51:43.301 --> 51:48.534
No, no, no, no, no.

51:48.639 --> 51:54.669
#<i>[Continues]</i>

52:08.459 --> 52:12.293
<i>[Indistinct Voices]</i>

52:24.075 --> 52:28.535
#<i>[Continues]</i>

52:44.195 --> 52:49.223
<i>[Indistinct Shouting]</i>

53:25.036 --> 53:28.938
- <i>Doing good. Up slow, Jerry.</i>
- <i>[Boy] Mommy, hurry up.!</i>

53:29.040 --> 53:31.474
- <i>[Man] I got it.</i>
- Not so fast.

53:31.576 --> 53:33.377
- Stop that sway. Easy.
- Come on, Mommy. Faster.

53:33.377 --> 53:33.968
- Stop that sway. Easy.
- Come on, Mommy. Faster.

53:34.078 --> 53:37.377
- Hold it. Stay clear, you guys.
- Oh! Wait. Wait!

53:37.481 --> 53:40.211
<i>[Boy]</i>
<i>My balloon.!</i>

53:40.318 --> 53:42.309
Sorry, kid.
It's gone to balloon heaven.

53:42.420 --> 53:45.287
That's okay, sir. We're gonna
get another one at the park.

53:45.389 --> 53:47.323
- Go ahead, honey.
- <i>Promise, Mommy?</i>

53:47.425 --> 53:50.553
<i>Comin'at you, guys.</i>
<i>Comin'your way.</i>

53:50.661 --> 53:54.392
You were here on Thursday, right?
You were moving the piano on Thursday too, right?

53:54.498 --> 53:56.966
- Can I help you with something?
- Yeah, the kid and the balloon-

53:57.068 --> 54:00.299
- The same thing happened on Thursday, right?
- We're a little busy here.

54:00.404 --> 54:02.372
Why don't you go bother
someone else, huh?

54:02.473 --> 54:06.637
Your way, guys! There you go.
Watch that thing. That's it.

54:11.449 --> 54:13.349
Christ!
Where have you been?

54:16.454 --> 54:18.445
What happened to you?

54:18.556 --> 54:21.923
I've been calling people all over the city,
looking for you.

54:22.026 --> 54:26.292
- I was about to call the police.
What happened to you?
- [Coughs]

54:26.397 --> 54:29.798
I've been calling people all over the city,
looking for you.

54:29.900 --> 54:32.198
Christ!
Where have you been?

54:32.303 --> 54:34.771
I've been calling people all over the city,
looking for you.

54:34.872 --> 54:38.035
<i>I was about to call the police.</i>
<i>What's going on, Sam?</i>

54:38.142 --> 54:41.236
- I don't know.
- No, you've gotta talk to me. I've been up all night.

54:41.345 --> 54:43.245
- What happened to your arm?
- Dog bite.

54:43.347 --> 54:45.577
- Dog bite?
- Yeah, I had the shots and the painkillers.

54:45.683 --> 54:48.413
- What dog? Where?
- Look, I'm seeing things
that don't make any sense...

54:48.519 --> 54:50.680
and I'm meeting people that
are supposed to be dead...

54:50.788 --> 54:52.688
and Beth's had
a nervous breakdown.

54:52.790 --> 54:55.691
The kid I'm treating knows
what's gonna happen before it happens.

54:55.793 --> 54:59.524
- Okay, just slow down.
- And I saw the same boy
lose the same balloon twice.

54:59.630 --> 55:02.497
- Baby, you're not making any sense.
- No, nothing makes any sense.

55:02.600 --> 55:04.830
- You're scaring me.
- Nothing makes any sense.

55:04.935 --> 55:08.132
Okay. You just need
to relax. Slow down.

55:08.239 --> 55:10.173
- Okay.
- Hey, you need to sleep.

55:10.274 --> 55:13.141
Yeah. No, I can't.

55:13.244 --> 55:15.644
- I gotta find him. I'm running out of time.
- No, no.

55:15.746 --> 55:18.214
- Just for a while. Lie down.
- You think?

55:18.316 --> 55:21.376
All right. All right.

55:21.485 --> 55:23.976
Maybe just for a little bit.

55:24.088 --> 55:26.921
- Okay.
- [Sighs]

55:27.024 --> 55:29.652
Maybe just a little bit.

56:11.602 --> 56:13.763
<i>[Keys Jingling]</i>

56:16.907 --> 56:18.807
Jesus Christ.

56:22.847 --> 56:25.543
<i>I've been looking all over for you.</i>

56:27.385 --> 56:30.752
I want you to come uptown with me.
I want you to meet a friend of mine.

56:32.723 --> 56:34.623
I don't wanna go uptown.

56:39.296 --> 56:41.457
I met your mother last night.

56:42.967 --> 56:45.834
What do you mean,
you met my mother?

56:45.936 --> 56:48.234
<i>You told me she was dead.</i>

56:48.339 --> 56:50.398
She's okay?

56:50.508 --> 56:52.271
<i>Yeah, everyone seems to think</i>
<i>your mother's dead...</i>

56:52.376 --> 56:54.537
but I'm standing in a kitchen
talking to her.

56:54.645 --> 56:56.442
Sh-She's gonna be okay?

56:56.547 --> 56:59.345
I don't know. She's sick.
She got hurt somehow. I don't know.

56:59.450 --> 57:01.782
Is she mad?

57:01.886 --> 57:04.354
- The dog seemed pretty fuckin' mad.
- What dog?

57:04.455 --> 57:08.323
- Olive.
- Olive?

57:08.426 --> 57:10.394
Yeah, we put Olive
to sleep when I was 12.

57:10.494 --> 57:12.359
She had a tumor in her liver.

57:12.463 --> 57:15.762
Well, Olive's not dead.
She is very much not dead.

57:15.866 --> 57:17.857
Yeah, she is.
But she was a good girl.

57:17.968 --> 57:20.630
Quit playing with me.
I wanna know what's going on.

57:20.738 --> 57:24.697
How do you know the future?
I wanna help you, but-

57:24.809 --> 57:26.544
- I need some fuckin' answers!
- What happened to your parents?

57:26.544 --> 57:28.068
- I need some fuckin' answers!
- What happened to your parents?

57:32.116 --> 57:36.951
Look, there are things that you have to tell me.
I mean, I mean...

57:37.054 --> 57:39.614
[Together] if you were just gonna
kill yourself, you'd have done it by now.

57:39.723 --> 57:42.715
[Together]
So why haven't you?

57:42.827 --> 57:46.228
Why do you keep coming to me?

57:46.330 --> 57:50.096
[Sighs]

57:50.201 --> 57:52.567
'Cause you're the only one
that can help me.

57:55.372 --> 57:57.363
That's why.

58:00.878 --> 58:03.438
<i>[Door Opens]</i>

58:07.551 --> 58:08.586
<i>Henry? Henry?</i>

58:08.586 --> 58:10.178
<i>Henry? Henry?</i>

58:10.287 --> 58:12.255
I've seen people go through
what you're going through.

58:14.024 --> 58:17.187
I've helped them come out
the other side.

58:17.294 --> 58:19.524
If you work with me,
I can help you.

58:23.968 --> 58:26.698
The way you helped your girl?

58:28.138 --> 58:30.971
<i>It's Lila, right?</i>

58:32.543 --> 58:36.309
I've seen the, uh,
scars on her wrists.

58:39.884 --> 58:42.375
Did you save her?

58:42.486 --> 58:45.614
<i>[Cigarette Lighter Lights]</i>

58:47.591 --> 58:49.525
She saved herself.

58:53.597 --> 58:56.191
Yeah, but you helped, right?

58:57.902 --> 59:02.498
No. Sometimes suicide is an attempt
for attention. With Lila it wasn't.

59:02.606 --> 59:05.769
<i>She put three four-inch vertical slits</i>
<i>in each wrist.</i>

59:05.876 --> 59:09.039
<i>She split both sets of ulnar</i>
<i>and radial arteries.</i>

59:09.146 --> 59:13.173
By the time I got to her,
she'd lost five pints of blood.

59:13.284 --> 59:16.549
<i>I just pulled her out of the bathtub,</i>
<i>put tourniquets on both arms...</i>

59:16.654 --> 59:19.487
<i>and called an ambulance.</i>

59:19.590 --> 59:21.888
Aren't you afraid
she's gonna do it again?

59:23.727 --> 59:25.922
No.

59:26.030 --> 59:27.930
Why?

59:29.600 --> 59:31.500
<i>'Cause she loves me.</i>

59:34.638 --> 59:39.234
<i>If she were here,</i>
<i>I know she'd say...</i>

59:39.343 --> 59:41.868
to open your eyes a little wider.

59:44.515 --> 59:47.916
<i>I know she'd tell you that</i>
<i>there's too much beauty to quit.</i>

59:57.127 --> 59:59.527
She's probably right.

01:00:00.798 --> 01:00:04.757
Anyway... it's too late.

01:00:06.337 --> 01:00:08.362
Henry?

01:00:08.472 --> 01:00:10.372
I can't let you leave this time.

01:00:10.474 --> 01:00:12.840
You gotta stay with me.
I gotta take you uptown to meet this-

01:00:12.943 --> 01:00:14.877
- Get the fuck outta my way.
- No, you gotta come with me to the-

01:00:14.979 --> 01:00:18.039
- Get outta my way, all right? Move. Move.
- I can't.

01:00:18.148 --> 01:00:20.981
- I can't let you-
- Let me show you something.

01:00:21.085 --> 01:00:24.646
- <i>[Cocks Gun]</i>
- [Breathing Heavily]

01:00:26.390 --> 01:00:29.450
I killed my parents.

01:00:34.098 --> 01:00:36.123
I killed my mother and my father.

01:00:36.233 --> 01:00:40.465
[Breathing Heavily]

01:00:40.571 --> 01:00:42.471
I'm gonna go to hell.

01:00:45.709 --> 01:00:48.644
Or maybe I'm already there.
I don't know.

01:00:53.951 --> 01:00:55.851
I'm sorry, Sam.

01:00:55.953 --> 01:00:57.853
[Uncocks Gun]

01:01:01.258 --> 01:01:03.158
Don't follow me.

01:01:29.420 --> 01:01:31.445
Canal Street.
A diner.

01:01:31.555 --> 01:01:33.523
Canal Street. A diner. Yeah, which diner?
There's maybe 20.

01:01:33.624 --> 01:01:36.787
I don't know, pick one.
Keep the meter running.

01:01:51.408 --> 01:01:54.639
Excuse me.
Do you have an Athena working here?

01:01:54.745 --> 01:01:57.236
Yeah. Athena!

01:01:57.347 --> 01:01:59.713
- Yeah, what?
- Athena?

01:01:59.817 --> 01:02:02.513
What? What do you want?

01:02:02.619 --> 01:02:05.713
All right, next one.
All right, next one.

01:02:07.691 --> 01:02:09.591
All right, next one.

01:02:14.665 --> 01:02:16.690
All right.

01:02:16.800 --> 01:02:18.700
There's one more.

01:02:20.504 --> 01:02:25.100
#<i>[Continues]</i>

01:02:25.209 --> 01:02:27.973
We're running out of options here.
I really don't know what you want.

01:02:28.078 --> 01:02:30.638
All right.
Just try one more, please.

01:02:33.283 --> 01:02:35.444
<i>[Thunderclap]</i>

01:02:45.362 --> 01:02:47.592
[ChangeJingles]

01:02:47.698 --> 01:02:50.724
Excuse me.
Do you have a waitress here named Athena?

01:02:50.834 --> 01:02:52.301
- Athena?
- Yeah.

01:02:52.402 --> 01:02:55.860
No, never heard of her.

01:02:57.174 --> 01:03:00.075
- Can I get a coffee, please?
- Sure.

01:03:15.025 --> 01:03:17.289
<i>[Woman]</i>
<i>Planning on proposing to Athena?</i>

01:03:19.863 --> 01:03:22.559
No. Do you know her?

01:03:22.666 --> 01:03:26.727
- <i>Are we talking about the same girl?</i>
- You a cop?

01:03:27.838 --> 01:03:30.306
No, I'm more of a matchmaker.

01:03:30.407 --> 01:03:33.934
<i>Doesn't work here anymore.</i>
<i>But she's in my acting class.</i>

01:03:35.179 --> 01:03:38.307
She is?
Could you tell me where she lives?

01:03:38.415 --> 01:03:40.246
What are you, her stalker?

01:03:40.350 --> 01:03:43.786
No. No.

01:03:43.887 --> 01:03:47.015
- <i>[Velcro Peels Apart]</i>
- I'm a psychiatrist.

01:03:47.124 --> 01:03:49.149
See?

01:03:49.259 --> 01:03:53.525
A psychiatrist, huh?
So you could write a Xanax prescription.

01:03:53.630 --> 01:03:56.360
I could write
a Xanax prescription...

01:03:56.466 --> 01:03:59.094
for one of my patients
who needed it, yeah.

01:03:59.203 --> 01:04:01.137
Okay.

01:04:01.238 --> 01:04:03.263
Good luck finding Athena.

01:04:06.677 --> 01:04:09.544
- <i>[Man] Prison, my lord?</i>
- Denmark's a prison.

01:04:09.646 --> 01:04:12.410
- Then is the world one?
- <i>A goodly one...</i>

01:04:12.516 --> 01:04:15.349
<i>in which there are many confines,</i>
<i>wards and dungeons.</i>

01:04:15.452 --> 01:04:18.046
Denmark being one of the worst.

01:04:18.155 --> 01:04:20.055
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>We think not so, my lord.</i>

01:04:20.157 --> 01:04:23.024
<i>Well, then 'tis none to you,</i>
<i>for there is nothing either good or bad...</i>

01:04:23.126 --> 01:04:25.026
but thinking makes it so.

01:04:25.128 --> 01:04:27.790
To me, it is a prison.

01:04:27.898 --> 01:04:30.230
- <i>Prison, my lord?</i>
- Denmark's a prison.

01:04:30.334 --> 01:04:32.962
- We already had this conversation.
- Oh, um, uh, wait a minute.

01:04:33.070 --> 01:04:37.302
Uh, um-

01:04:37.407 --> 01:04:41.309
- "Why then your ambition"-
- Why then your ambition makes it one.

01:04:41.411 --> 01:04:43.470
'Tis too narrow for your mind.

01:04:43.580 --> 01:04:45.480
I could be bounded
in a nutshell...

01:04:45.582 --> 01:04:48.016
and count myself
a king of infinite space...

01:04:48.118 --> 01:04:51.349
<i>were it not</i>
<i>that I have bad dreams.</i>

01:04:51.455 --> 01:04:55.482
- That's my favorite line in the whole play.
- <i>It's a good line.</i>

01:04:55.592 --> 01:04:58.026
